Quote:  Col. Gold was more lucky than some people suspected in getting such a lumbering train home safely. He now says it was only a reconnoitering party and nothing more, but as he had previously been down with a light and suitable escort to look at the pas and then ordered a bullet proof machine to be made (mantelette I believe it is called, how spelt I know) people don't believe this statement; ...
Notes:  (James M. Atkinson)
